Program: Omnibus
Title: Hana's Suitcase
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p0376m8d
Last Broadcast Date: 23 August 2001
The story of Hana Brady’s death in Auschwitz concentration camp. How children’s belongings from Auschwitz Museum used in an exhibition in Japan brought her story to light. With contributions from exhibition organiser Fumiko Ishioka and Hana’s brother George.